The paper deals with compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). However, the use of generative models and deep learning techniques suggests that it could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The construction of a ReLU-based neural network also suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of lower bounds and complexity analysis suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
